headline: JPMorgan price target raised to $254 from $216 at Keefe Bruyette
summary: Keefe Bruyette raised the firm’s price target on JPMorgan (JPM) to $254 from $216 and keeps a Market Perform rating on the shares. The U.S. bank stocks have had a strong run following better than expected earnings and, more importantly, the election results, the analyst tells investors in a research note.
